Class CleverSearcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • searcher.Searcher
      • searcher.CleverSearcher
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CleverSearcherTimer

    public class CleverSearcher
extends Searcher
    Implements the find (kth) element method by making a smaller array of size K, sorts it, then comparing the larger arrays values to the small array, to see if ones bigger. Which then swaps it out
    Version:
    October 2019
    Author:
    Molly Price

        public int findElement()
                throws searcher.IndexingError
        • Make an array of size k and copy first 5 values of big array into it
        • Sort small array
        • Loop through array and check if big array[k] is smaller than smallest index of small array starting from k
        • If it is then move on to next number, otherwise loop through small array and place big array[k] before number that is bigger than it.
        • Remove smallest from small array
        • Repeat through big array
        • Return the entry at start of small array
